rrectly.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Exploring LegacyDiscoveredScriptTemplate**\\n\\nThe parent application can load `LegacyDiscoveredScriptTemplate`, and it likely already has since `LegacyDiscoveredScriptTemplate::class.java` is in use. This simplifies things by removing the need for `getResourceAsStream` and related imports. Now, I should implement this with ASM, needing imports like `org.jetbrains.org.objectweb.asm.ClassWriter` and possibly `Opcodes`. It's good that the target compile can access `org.jetbrains.org.objectweb.asm`, and since the target class uses shaded ASM, I need to ensure it is compatible. I have to be careful with Kotlin's named `type.internalName` as a helper for the code.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_DTEK1Nl7Nvrx9imSGsF0ltWt|fc_07e37d872963455d016a2a1e57ad448195b6571982f7bbb17e", "name": "edit", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/org.jetbrains.kotlin/kotlin-scripting-compiler-impl-embeddable/2.3.21/src/test/kotlin/org_jetbrains_kotlin/kotlin_scripting_compiler_impl_embeddable/ScriptiDefinitionsFromClasspathDiscoverySourceKtTest.kt", "edits": [{"oldText": "import java.io.InputStream\nimport java.nio.file.Files\n", "newText": "import java.nio.file.Files\n"}, {"oldText": "import org.jetbrains.kotlin.scripting.definitions.discoverScriptTemplatesInClasspath\nimport org.jetbrains.kotlin.scripting.definitions.loadScriptTemplatesFromClasspath\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Test\n", "newText": "import org.jetbrains.kotlin.scripting.definitions.discoverScriptTemplatesInClasspath\nimport org.jetbrains.kotlin.scripting.definitions.loadScriptTemplatesFromClasspath\nimport org.jetbrains.org.objectweb.asm.ClassWriter\nimport org.jetbrains.org.objectweb.asm.Opcodes\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Test\n"}, {"oldText": "        val classResourceName: String = type.name.replace('.', '/') + \".class\"\n        val classFile: Path = root.resolve(classResourceName)\n        Files.createDirectories(classFile.parent)\n        requireNotNull(t